ContainedObjects.Description: If an attack hits, the attacker rolls the damage dice listed for his weapon plus 1/2 or 1/3rd of his strength depending on the weapon. If the D20 roll to attack is high enough, it may be a critical hit that deals double damage. Crits usually cause extra effects like bleeding.  Many status effects require a saving throw to avoid the bad stuff happening.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
In combat you will roll 1D20 to attack. Magic weapons and weapon skills can improve your attack roll. 
When enemies attack you, they need a result higher than your dodge. The defender wins ties. 
various skills and situations can modify your chances of hitting with an attack or doding enemy attacks.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description: Armor and Weapons are listed on boards and color coded by material type. Stone, Bone, Wood, Cloth, Metal, Leather, Fur. items can be made of various different materials of different qualities that modify the base stats of the item. The default materials are Linen, cattle-hide, oak and iron. Materials change item weight, price, armor points, damage resistance, damage dice, and enchantability.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Saves equal half the relevant attribute.
Round down if you get fractions.
Strength save: 1 (grapple, Wind)
Speed save: 2 (attacks, gravity)
Body save: 2 (poison, fire)
Mind save: 1 (sleep, Blind)
when prompted, roll 1D20 and add your save bonus. Various skills and items can add to these saves.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Attributes are listed like "2 + 0" because you have a base value and then a bonus added by enchantments. When you choose a race and 3 skills your base values will change.
you can carry 8 + 2x Strength, you have 5 HP per body point and 5 MP per mind point. Dodge equals speed. strength adds bonus damage 1/3rd Strength for 1 handed weapons or 1/2 for two handed weapons.
